            "summary": "Burning Rock Biotech Limited reported financial results for the three months ended March 31, 2025, including revenues of RMB133.1 million (US$18.3 million), which was a 5.9% increase from the same period in 2024. Revenue from central laboratory business was RMB38.3 million (US$5.3 million), down 19.6%, while revenue from pharma research and development services was RMB37.1 million (US$5.1 million), up 79.9%. Operating expenses decreased by 46.8%, with net loss at RMB13.5 million (US$1.9 million) for the period. Cash, cash equivalents, and restricted cash were RMB497.4 million (US$68.5 million) as of March 31, 2025. Burning Rock focuses on precision oncology with next-generation sequencing technology. Study results were presented for various cancers at conferences. The company continues to advance its products and services in the field of oncology.",
            "source_type": "news",
            "headline": "Burning Rock Biotech reported Q1 2025: Revenue of RMB133.1 million (US$18.3 million), a 5.9% increase from last year. Net loss RMB13.5 million (US$1.9 million). Gross profit RMB97.4 million (US$13.4 million), with gross margin at 73.2%. Operating expenses RMB112.6 million (US$15.5 million), a 46.8% decrease from last year. Contact IR@brbiotech.com for more.",
